---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config/site';
---
<Layout
  title={`Methodology | ${SITE.name}`}
  description="Compute Current methodology for crawler sources, extraction quality, infrastructure relevance, taxonomy assignment, editorial blueprints, repetition checks, and indexing safeguards."
  canonicalPath="/methodology/"
>
  <main class="policy-shell">
    <a class="back-link" href="/">Intelligence board</a>
    <article class="policy-page">
      <p class="eyebrow">Methodology</p>
      <h1>How Compute Current turns source reporting into infrastructure signals.</h1>
      <p class="policy-lede">
        The pipeline is designed to separate source facts from interpretation, classify infrastructure relevance, and prevent low-quality generated pages from being treated as durable editorial assets.
      </p>

      <section>
        <h2>1. Source Collection</h2>
        <p>
          Crawled source articles are normalized with their title, URL, source name, publication time, extracted body text, source image, and source domain adapter when available.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>2. Extraction QA</h2>
        <p>
          Each source is scored for content length, boilerplate ratio, title-body similarity, copyright footer detection, navigation or CTA detection, sentence completion, source-domain adapter fit, and total extraction quality.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>3. Infrastructure Relevance</h2>
        <p>
          Articles are scored for direct AI infrastructure relevance, data center relevance, cloud capacity relevance, semiconductor relevance, power and grid relevance, cooling relevance, capital markets relevance, and enterprise AI infrastructure relevance.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>4. Taxonomy and Briefing Shape</h2>
        <p>
          Qualified items receive a primary category, secondary category, infrastructure layer, affected stakeholders, article type, region, urgency score, and article blueprint. Blueprint selection is constrained so consecutive article structures do not become repetitive.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>5. Publication and Indexing</h2>
        <p>
          High-relevance, high-quality articles can become full Compute Current memos. Medium-relevance items are treated as short signal cards. Low-relevance items are archived and should not surface on the homepage unless manually approved. Generated pages with explicit low extraction quality or low relevance are marked noindex.
        </p>
      </section>

      <nav class="policy-link-row" aria-label="Transparency pages">
        <a href="/about/">About</a>
        <a href="/editorial-policy/">Editorial Policy</a>
        <a href="/ai-disclosure/">AI-assisted Disclosure</a>
      </nav>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>
